Rule 1: NEVER enable, disable, skip, unskip, comment out, uncomment, or otherwise change the enablement status of any test suite, test case, or test runner script. If a test is disabled, it was disabled intentionally. If a test is enabled and flaky, fix the test â€” do not disable it.
Rule 2: NEVER modify CI scripts (.github/scripts/tests-*/**/run-tests.*) or workflow YAML files to change which tests run or on which platforms they run.
Rule 3: The set of tests that run is NEVER the agent's decision. Always leave test enablement as-is.
